wfmpsDelete.name: wfmpsDelete
wfmpsDelete.description: Indication to create or delete an MPS base Entry from the MIB

wfmpsSlot.name: wfmpsSlot
wfmpsSlot.description: The Slot number of the slot on which this MPS is instantiated.

wfmpsCct.name: wfmpsCct
wfmpsCct.description: This corresponds to the circuit number associated with the ATM Driver

wfmpsCacheIpOverRide.name: wfmpsCacheIpOverRide
wfmpsCacheIpOverRide.description: Indicates whether the wfmps defined MPS Egress Cache reverification timer over rides the timer defined by the wfIpInterfaceHostCache.i If on, overide and use the timer defined by wfmpsCacheReverifyTimer if off, use the timer defined by wfIpInterfaceHostCache.

wfmpsCacheReverifyTimer.name: wfmpsCacheReverifyTimer
wfmpsCacheReverifyTimer.description: A range of values to specify the timer value for MPS Egress Cache reverification. This value is of significance, only when wfmpsCacheIpOverRide is turned on.

wfmpsAddrGenerateMode.name: wfmpsAddrGenerateMode
wfmpsAddrGenerateMode.description: Indicates whether this MPS's address should be generated automatically or manually.

wfmpsConfigTable.name: wfmpsConfigTable
wfmpsConfigTable.description: The MPOA Server Configuration Table. This table represents the configuration information for all MPOA Servers which this agent manages.

wfmpsConfigEntry.name: wfmpsConfigEntry
wfmpsConfigEntry.description: MPOA Server Configuration Entry. Each entry contains configuration information for one MPOA Server Control.

wfmpsCnfDelete.name: wfmpsCnfDelete
wfmpsCnfDelete.description: Indication to create or delete an MPS Config Entry from the MIB

wfmpsRowStatus.name: wfmpsRowStatus
wfmpsRowStatus.description: This object allows creation and deletion of MPOA Servers. Within each conceptual wfmpsConfigTable row, objects which are writable may be modified regardless of the value of wfmpsRowStatus. It is not necessary to set a row's status to 'notInService' first. A row cannot be created, unless the wfmpsAtmCtrlAddress in this table is unique. When an MPOA Server is created via this object, it will initially have 'wfmpsOperStatus' = 'initialState'

wfmpsCnfIndex.name: wfmpsCnfIndex
wfmpsCnfIndex.description: A value which uniquely identifies this conceptual row in the wfmpsConfigTable. The 'wfmpsNextIndex' object needs to be used to determine the value of this object. A row cannot be added, unless wfmpsCtrlAtmAddr is unique. In the event of an MPS re-initialization, the value of this wfmpsIndex must remain the same. However, in the event of an agent re-initialization, this value does not need to be preserved.

wfmpsConfigMode.name: wfmpsConfigMode
wfmpsConfigMode.description: Indicates whether this MPS should auto-configure the next time it is (re-)initialized. In automatic(1) mode the LECS is contacted and requests are made for the MPS-p* parameters as indicated by wfmpsConfigMask. In manual(2) mode, the values of the configuration parameters are obtained from the wfmpsConfigTable and the wfmpsProtocolTable.

wfmpsCtrlAtmAddr.name: wfmpsCtrlAtmAddr
wfmpsCtrlAtmAddr.description: The MPS's Control ATM Address. There exists one Control ATM Address per MPS, therefore, the value of this entry is unique within the table.

wfmpsKeepAliveTime.name: wfmpsKeepAliveTime
wfmpsKeepAliveTime.description: MPS-p1 Keep-alive time is max interval between the MPS sending MPOA Keep-Alives in seconds.

wfmpsKeepAliveLifeTime.name: wfmpsKeepAliveLifeTime
wfmpsKeepAliveLifeTime.description: MPS-p2 Keep-Alive Lifetime The length of time an MPC may consider a Keep-Alive valid in seconds. This value must be at least three times the wfmpsKeepAliveTime (MPS-p1).

wfmpsInitialRetryTime.name: wfmpsInitialRetryTime
wfmpsInitialRetryTime.description: MPS-p4 is initial value in seconds for the MPOA retry mechanism.

wfmpsRetryTimeMaximum.name: wfmpsRetryTimeMaximum
wfmpsRetryTimeMaximum.reference: Multiprotocol Over ATM. AF-MPOA-0087.000. Section 4.3 MPOA Retry Mechanism
wfmpsRetryTimeMaximum.description: MPS-p5 cumulative max value in seconds for Retry Time (MPS-p4).

wfmpsGiveupTime.name: wfmpsGiveupTime
wfmpsGiveupTime.description: MPS-p6 Give Up Time. Minimum time in seconds to wait before giving up on a pending resolution request.

wfmpsDefaultHoldingTime.name: wfmpsDefaultHoldingTime
wfmpsDefaultHoldingTime.description: MPS-p7 Default Holding Time in minutes. The default Holding Time used in NHRP Resolution Replies. An egress MPS may use local information to determine a more appropriate Holding Time.

wfmpsCnfSlot.name: wfmpsCnfSlot
wfmpsCnfSlot.description: The Slot number of the slot on which this MPS is instantiated.

wfmpsInitialCacheSize.name: wfmpsInitialCacheSize
wfmpsInitialCacheSize.description: Indicates the amount of memory to allocate initially to accomadate the cache entries.

wfmpsMaxCacheSize.name: wfmpsMaxCacheSize
wfmpsMaxCacheSize.description: Maximum number of Ingress/Egress cache entries allowed

wfmpsLECSAddress.name: wfmpsLECSAddress
wfmpsLECSAddress.description: The LE Config Server Address to be used. If left(or set) to NULL_VAL the well-known LECS ATM address will be used.

wfmpsDebugMsgLevel.name: wfmpsDebugMsgLevel
wfmpsDebugMsgLevel.description: Debug Levels - This attribute is used to assign the level of DEBUG message to be logged for each MPS.

wfmpsActualTable.name: wfmpsActualTable
wfmpsActualTable.description: A read-only table containing identification, status, and operational information about the MPOA Servers this agent manages.

wfmpsActualEntry.name: wfmpsActualEntry
wfmpsActualEntry.description: An entry in the MPS Actual Table. An entry represents a specific MPOA Server's status and operation information.

wfmpsActualState.name: wfmpsActualState
wfmpsActualState.description: This object indicates the current operational status of the MPOA Server.

wfmpsDiscontinuityTime.name: wfmpsDiscontinuityTime
wfmpsDiscontinuityTime.description: The value of sysUpTime on the most recent occasion at which any one or more of this MPS's counters experienced a discontinuity. The relevant counters are the specific instances associated with this MPS. If discontinuities have not occurred since the last re-initialization of the local management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

wfmpsActualConfigMode.name: wfmpsActualConfigMode
wfmpsActualConfigMode.description: Indicates whether this MPS auto-configured when it started was last (re-)initialized. In automatic(1) mode the LECS was contacted and all the MPS-p* parameters were downloaded. In manual(2) mode, either the LECS could not be contacted (if wfmpsConfigMode is automatic) or local over rides are being used (wfmpsConfigMode is manual). if wfmpsConfigMode is automatic and wfmpsActualConfigMode is manual, then the initial values are the MIB defaults. As always, any values can be set, however, if wfmpsConfigMode is automatic, those changes will be lost on the next restart.

wfmpsActualKeepAlive.name: wfmpsActualKeepAlive
wfmpsActualKeepAlive.description: The maximum amount of time in seconds this MPS waits between sending MPOA Keep-Alives.

wfmpsActualKeepAliveLifeTime.name: wfmpsActualKeepAliveLifeTime
wfmpsActualKeepAliveLifeTime.description: The length of time in seconds this MPS considers a Keep-Alive valid.

wfmpsActualInitialRetryTime.name: wfmpsActualInitialRetryTime
wfmpsActualInitialRetryTime.description: The actual initial value in seconds for the MPOA retry mechanism.

wfmpsActualRetryTimeMaximum.name: wfmpsActualRetryTimeMaximum
wfmpsActualRetryTimeMaximum.reference: Multiprotocol Over ATM. AF-MPOA-0087.000. Section 4.3 MPOA Retry Mechanism
wfmpsActualRetryTimeMaximum.description: The actual cumulative max value in seconds for Retry Time.

wfmpsActualGiveupTime.name: wfmpsActualGiveupTime
wfmpsActualGiveupTime.description: Minimum time in seconds that this MPS waits before giving up on a pending resolution request.

wfmpsActualDefaultHoldingTime.name: wfmpsActualDefaultHoldingTime
wfmpsActualDefaultHoldingTime.description: The actual Holding Time in minutes used in NHRP Resolution Replies.

wfmpsActSlot.name: wfmpsActSlot
wfmpsActSlot.description: The Slot number of the slot on which this MPS is instantiated.

wfmpsActualCtrlAtmAddr.name: wfmpsActualCtrlAtmAddr
wfmpsActualCtrlAtmAddr.description: The Actual MPS's Control ATM Address. There exists one Control ATM Address per MPS, therefore, the value of this entry is unique within the table.

wfmpsStatisticsTable.name: wfmpsStatisticsTable
wfmpsStatisticsTable.description: This table represents the statistical information for the MPSs, which this agent manages.

wfmpsStatisticsEntry.name: wfmpsStatisticsEntry
wfmpsStatisticsEntry.description: Each row in this table contains statistics for one MPOA server.

wfmpsStatRxMpoaResolveRequests.name: wfmpsStatRxMpoaResolveRequests
wfmpsStatRxMpoaResolveRequests.description: The number of MPOA Resolve Requests received by this MPS which are translated to NHRP resolve requests. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and/or re-initialization of the MPS, and at other times, as indicated by the value of wfmpsDiscontinuityTime.

wfmpsStatTxMpoaResolveReplyAcks.name: wfmpsStatTxMpoaResolveReplyAcks
wfmpsStatTxMpoaResolveReplyAcks.description: The number of MPOA Resolve Replies transmitted by this MPS which contain the MPOA CIE Code of 0x00 - Success. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and/or re-initialization of the MPS, and at other times, as indicated by the value of mpsDiscontinuityTime.

wfmpsStatTxMpoaResolveReplyInsufECResour.name: wfmpsStatTxMpoaResolveReplyInsufECResources
wfmpsStatTxMpoaResolveReplyInsufECResour.description: The number of MPOA Resolve Replies transmitted by this MPS which contain the MPOA CIE Code of 0x81 - Insufficient resources to accept egress cache entry. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and/or re-initialization of the MPS, and at other times, as indicated by the value of mpsDiscontinuityTime.

wfmpsStatTxMpoaResolveReplyInsufSCResour.name: wfmpsStatTxMpoaResolveReplyInsufSCResources
wfmpsStatTxMpoaResolveReplyInsufSCResour.description: The number of MPOA Resolve Replies transmitted by this MPS which contain the MPOA CIE Code of 0x82 - Insufficent resources to accept shortcut. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and/or re-initialization of the MPS, and at other times, as indicated by the value of mpsDiscontinuityTime.

wfmpsStatTxMpoaResolveReplyInsufEitherRe.name: wfmpsStatTxMpoaResolveReplyInsufEitherResources
wfmpsStatTxMpoaResolveReplyInsufEitherRe.description: The number of MPOA Resolve Replies transmitted by this MPS which contain the MPOA CIE CODE of 0x83 - Insufficient resources to accept either shortcut or egress cache entry. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and/or re-initialization of the MPS, and at other times, as indicated by the value of mpsDiscontinuityTime.

wfmpsStatTxMpoaResolveReplyUnsupportedIn.name: wfmpsStatTxMpoaResolveReplyUnsupportedInetProt
wfmpsStatTxMpoaResolveReplyUnsupportedIn.description: The number of MPOA Resolve Replies transmitted by this MPS which contain the MPOA CIE CODE of 0x84 - Unsupported Internetwork Layer protocol. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and/or re-initialization of the MPS, and at other times, as indicated by the value of mpsDiscontinuityTime.

wfmpsStatTxMpoaResolveReplyUnsupportedMa.name: wfmpsStatTxMpoaResolveReplyUnsupportedMacEncaps
wfmpsStatTxMpoaResolveReplyUnsupportedMa.description: The number of MPOA Resolve Replies transmitted by this MPS which contain the MPOA CIE CODE of 0x85 - Unsupported MAC layer encapsulation. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and/or re-initialization of the MPS, and at other times, as indicated by the value of mpsDiscontinuityTime.

wfmpsStatTxMpoaResolveReplyUnspecifiedOt.name: wfmpsStatTxMpoaResolveReplyUnspecifiedOther
wfmpsStatTxMpoaResolveReplyUnspecifiedOt.description: The number of MPOA Resolve Replies transmitted by this MPS which contain the MPOA CIE CODE of 0x88 - Unspecified/Other. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and/or re-initialization of the MPS, and at other times, as indicated by the value of mpsDiscontinuityTime.

wfmpsStatTxMpoaResolveReplyOther.name: wfmpsStatTxMpoaResolveReplyOther
wfmpsStatTxMpoaResolveReplyOther.description: The number of MPOA Resolve Replies transmitted by this MPS which are not counted above. NOTE - this would include NHRP errors. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and/or re-initialization of the MPS, and at other times, as indicated by the value of mpsDiscontinuityTime.

wfmpsStatGiveupTimeExpireds.name: wfmpsStatGiveupTimeExpireds
wfmpsStatGiveupTimeExpireds.description: The number of times the MPS Give up Time (MPS-p6) has expired while waiting for a reply from a re-originated MPOA resolution request, i.e. a reply for a translated NHRP resolution request. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and/or re-initialization of the MPS, and at other times, as indicated by the value of mpsDiscontinuityTime.

wfmpsStatTxMpoaImpRequests.name: wfmpsStatTxMpoaImpRequests
wfmpsStatTxMpoaImpRequests.description: The number of MPOA Cache Imposition Requests transmitted by this MPS. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and/or re-initialization of the MPS, and at other times, as indicated by the value of mpsDiscontinuityTime.

wfmpsStatRxMpoaImpReplyAcks.name: wfmpsStatRxMpoaImpReplyAcks
wfmpsStatRxMpoaImpReplyAcks.description: The number of successful MPOA Cache Imposition Replies received by this MPS which contain an MPOA CIE Code of 0x00, Success. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and/or re-initialization of the MPS, and at other times, as indicated by the value of mpsDiscontinuityTime.

wfmpsStatRxMpoaImpReplyInsufECResources.name: wfmpsStatRxMpoaImpReplyInsufECResources
wfmpsStatRxMpoaImpReplyInsufECResources.description: The number of MPOA Cache Imposition Replies received by this MPS which contain the MPOA CIE Code of 0x81, Insufficient resources to accept egress cache entry. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and/or re-initialization of the MPS, and at other times, as indicated by the value of mpsDiscontinuityTime.

wfmpsStatRxMpoaImpReplyInsufSCResources.name: wfmpsStatRxMpoaImpReplyInsufSCResources
wfmpsStatRxMpoaImpReplyInsufSCResources.description: The number of MPOA Cache Imposition Replies received by this MPS which contain the MPOA CIE Code of 0x82 - Insufficient resources to accept shortcut. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and/or re-initialization of the MPS, and at other times, as indicated by the value of mpsDiscontinuityTime.

wfmpsStatRxMpoaImpReplyInsufEitherResour.name: wfmpsStatRxMpoaImpReplyInsufEitherResources
wfmpsStatRxMpoaImpReplyInsufEitherResour.description: The number of MPOA Cache Imposition Replies received by this MPS which contain the MPOA CIE Code of 0x83 - Insufficient resources to accept either shortcut or egress cache entry. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and/or re-initialization of the MPS, and at other times, as indicated by the value of mpsDiscontinuityTime.

wfmpsStatRxMpoaImpReplyUnsupportedInetPr.name: wfmpsStatRxMpoaImpReplyUnsupportedInetProt
wfmpsStatRxMpoaImpReplyUnsupportedInetPr.description: The number of MPOA Cache Imposition Replies received by this MPS which contain the MPOA CIE Code of 0x84 - Unsupported Internetwork Layer protocol. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and/or re-initialization of the MPS, and at other times, as indicated by the value of mpsDiscontinuityTime.

wfmpsStatRxMpoaImpReplyUnsupportedMacEnc.name: wfmpsStatRxMpoaImpReplyUnsupportedMacEncaps
wfmpsStatRxMpoaImpReplyUnsupportedMacEnc.description: The number of MPOA Cache Imposition Replies received by this MPS which contain the MPOA CIE Code of 0x85 - Unsupported MAC layer encapsulation. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and/or re-initialization of the MPS, and at other times, as indicated by the value of mpsDiscontinuityTime.

wfmpsStatRxMpoaImpReplyUnspecifiedOther.name: wfmpsStatRxMpoaImpReplyUnspecifiedOther
wfmpsStatRxMpoaImpReplyUnspecifiedOther.description: The number of MPOA Cache Imposition Replies received by this MPS which contain the MPOA CIE Code of 0x88 - Unspecified/Other. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and/or re-initialization of the MPS, and at other times, as indicated by the value of mpsDiscontinuityTime.

wfmpsStatRxMpoaImpReplyOther.name: wfmpsStatRxMpoaImpReplyOther
wfmpsStatRxMpoaImpReplyOther.description: The number of MPOA Cache Imposition Replies received by this MPS which are not counted previously. NOTE - this would include NHRP errors. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and/or re-initialization of the MPS, and at other times, as indicated by the value of mpsDiscontinuityTime.

wfmpsStatRxMpoaEgressCachePurgeRequests.name: wfmpsStatRxMpoaEgressCachePurgeRequests
wfmpsStatRxMpoaEgressCachePurgeRequests.description: The number of MPOA Egress Cache Purges Requests received by this MPS. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and/or re-initialization of the MPS, and at other times, as indicated by the value of mpsDiscontinuityTime.

wfmpsStatTxMpoaEgressCachePurgeReplies.name: wfmpsStatTxMpoaEgressCachePurgeReplies
wfmpsStatTxMpoaEgressCachePurgeReplies.description: The number of MPOA Egress Cache Purge Replies transmitted by this MPS. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and/or re-initialization of the MPS, and at other times, as indicated by the value of mpsDiscontinuityTime.

wfmpsStatTxMpoaTriggers.name: wfmpsStatTxMpoaTriggers
wfmpsStatTxMpoaTriggers.reference: Multiprotocol Over ATM. AF-MPOA-0087.000. Section 4.7.2.1 MPOA Trigger
wfmpsStatTxMpoaTriggers.description: The number of MPOA Trigger messages transmitted by this MPS. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and/or re-initialization of the MPS, and at other times, as indicated by the value of mpsDiscontinuityTime.

wfmpsStatTxNhrpResolveRequests.name: wfmpsStatTxNhrpResolveRequests
wfmpsStatTxNhrpResolveRequests.reference: Multiprotocol Over ATM. AF-MPOA-0087.000. Section 4.7.2.1 MPOA Trigger
wfmpsStatTxNhrpResolveRequests.description: Total count of MPOA Resolution Requests received by the Ingress MPS which were translated to NHRP Resolution Requests and transmitted to the NHS. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and/or re-initialization of the MPS, and at other times, as indicated by the value of mpsDiscontinuityTime.

wfmpsStatRxNhrpResolveReplies.name: wfmpsStatRxNhrpResolveReplies
wfmpsStatRxNhrpResolveReplies.reference: Multiprotocol Over ATM. AF-MPOA-0087.000. Section 4.7.2.1 MPOA Trigger
wfmpsStatRxNhrpResolveReplies.description: Total count of NHRP Resolution Replies received by the Ingress. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and/or re-initialization of the MPS, and at other times, as indicated by the value of mpsDiscontinuityTime.

wfmpsStatRxNhrpResolveRequests.name: wfmpsStatRxNhrpResolveRequests
wfmpsStatRxNhrpResolveRequests.reference: Multiprotocol Over ATM. AF-MPOA-0087.000. Section 4.7.2.1 MPOA Trigger
wfmpsStatRxNhrpResolveRequests.description: Total count of NHRP Resolution Requests received by the Egress MPS from the NHS. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and/or re-initialization of the MPS, and at other times, as indicated by the value of mpsDiscontinuityTime.

wfmpsStatTxNhrpResolveReplies.name: wfmpsStatTxNhrpResolveReplies
wfmpsStatTxNhrpResolveReplies.reference: Multiprotocol Over ATM. AF-MPOA-0087.000. Section 4.7.2.1 MPOA Trigger
wfmpsStatTxNhrpResolveReplies.description: Total count of NHRP Resolution Replies transmitted by the Egress MPS to the NHS. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and/or re-initialization of the MPS, and at other times, as indicated by the value of mpsDiscontinuityTime.

wfmpsStatSlot.name: wfmpsStatSlot
wfmpsStatSlot.description: The Slot number of the slot on which this MPS is instantiated.

wfmpsProtocolTable.name: wfmpsProtocolTable
wfmpsProtocolTable.reference: Multiprotocol Over ATM Version 1.0 (Letter Ballot), Section 4.1.1.1 MPS Parameters
wfmpsProtocolTable.description: List of protocols, per MPS, for which MPOA resolution is enabled.

wfmpsProtocolEntry.name: wfmpsProtocolEntry
wfmpsProtocolEntry.description: Each row indicates one protocol for which an MPS will perform MPOA resolution. If the corresponding MPS entry in wfmpsStatusTable has wfmpsActualConfigMode set to automatic, and the appropriate bit in wfmpsActualConfigMask (MPS-p3, bit 3) is set to 1, then values retrieved from the LECS are reflected in this table and the wfmpsLECSValue object will be (1) true. Also, the user can create rows which appropriately correspond to the MPS denoted by wfmpsIndex, and the wfmpsLECSValue object will be set to (2) false. NOTE - if the LECS does not return information for the MPS-p3 parameter, or if in manual mode, the user should create at least one entry for the corresponding MPS. Both, LECS and user-created rows may exist in this Table. This means that if the MPS was last re-initialized in in automatic mode (see wfmpsActualConfigMode), the set of rows is a union of values retreived from the LECS and manually configured.

wfmpsProtocolDelete.name: wfmpsProtocolDelete
wfmpsProtocolDelete.description: Indication to create or delete an MPS Protocol Entry from the MIB

wfmpsProtocolRowStatus.name: wfmpsProtocolRowStatus
wfmpsProtocolRowStatus.description: This object allows network managers to enable resolution for the 'wfmpsInternetworkLayerProtocol'.

wfmpsInternetworkLayerProtocol.name: wfmpsInternetworkLayerProtocol
wfmpsInternetworkLayerProtocol.description: MPS-p3 A protocol on which to perform MPOA resolution.

wfmpsLECSValue.name: wfmpsLECSValue
wfmpsLECSValue.description: This object reflects if the current entry is due to a retrieval from the LECS or not. If this entry is due to the LECS, then true(1) is the value for this object, otherwise, false (2).

wfmpsProtSlot.name: wfmpsProtSlot
wfmpsProtSlot.description: The Slot number of the slot on which this MPS is instantiated.

wfmpsMappingTable.name: wfmpsMappingTable
wfmpsMappingTable.description: A table mapping the 'lecIndex' values of LANE Clients to the 'wfmpsIndex' values of corresponding MPOA Servers.

wfmpsMappingEntry.name: wfmpsMappingEntry
wfmpsMappingEntry.reference: LAN Emulation Client Management Specification. af-lane-0044-000.
wfmpsMappingEntry.description: Each row defines one lecIndex --> wfmpsIndex mapping. The wfmpsIndex that a lecIndex maps to is not necessarily unique. In other words, there can be multiple LECs associated with one MPS.

wfmpsMappingDelete.name: wfmpsMappingDelete
wfmpsMappingDelete.description: Indication to create or delete an MPS Mapping Entry from the MIB

wfmpsMappingRowStatus.name: wfmpsMappingRowStatus
wfmpsMappingRowStatus.description: Allows creation, enabling/disabling of this row.

wfmpsMapIndex.name: wfmpsMapIndex
wfmpsMapIndex.description: The wfmpsMapIndex of the MPOA Server that is associated with this LEC. The wfmpsMapIndex corresponds to the wfmpsIndex.

wfmpsMapSlot.name: wfmpsMapSlot
wfmpsMapSlot.description: The Slot number of the slot on which this MPS is instantiated.

wfmpsIngressCacheTable.name: wfmpsIngressCacheTable
wfmpsIngressCacheTable.description: This table tracks all the Ingress Cache information of the MPSs which this agents manages.

wfmpsIngressCacheEntry.name: wfmpsIngressCacheEntry
wfmpsIngressCacheEntry.description: A entry contains parameters and state variables for a row in a MPS's Ingress Cache.

wfmpsIngressCacheDestInternetworkAddrTyp.name: wfmpsIngressCacheDestInternetworkAddrType
wfmpsIngressCacheDestInternetworkAddrTyp.description: The type of internetwork layer address of the Destination Address.

wfmpsIngressCacheDestAddr.name: wfmpsIngressCacheDestAddr
wfmpsIngressCacheDestAddr.description: The Ingress MPS Destination Internetwork Layer Address.

wfmpsIngressCachePrefixLen.name: wfmpsIngressCachePrefixLen
wfmpsIngressCachePrefixLen.description: The Prefix Length of the wfmpsIngressCacheDestAddr.

wfmpsIngressCacheSrcInternetworkAddrType.name: wfmpsIngressCacheSrcInternetworkAddrType
wfmpsIngressCacheSrcInternetworkAddrType.description: The type of internetwork layer address of the Source Address.

wfmpsIngressCacheSrcAddr.name: wfmpsIngressCacheSrcAddr
wfmpsIngressCacheSrcAddr.description: The Ingress MPS Source Internetwork Layer Address.

wfmpsIngressCacheSourceMpcAtmAddr.name: wfmpsIngressCacheSourceMpcAtmAddr
wfmpsIngressCacheSourceMpcAtmAddr.description: The ATM Adress from the source of this MPOA request. In other words, the Ingress MPC's Control Atm Address.

wfmpsIngressCacheResolvedAtmAddr.name: wfmpsIngressCacheResolvedAtmAddr
wfmpsIngressCacheResolvedAtmAddr.description: The ATM Adress which has been resolved by an Egress MPC.

wfmpsIngressCacheHoldTime.name: wfmpsIngressCacheHoldTime
wfmpsIngressCacheHoldTime.description: Time interval that this value is valid.

wfmpsIngressCacheMpoaRequestId.name: wfmpsIngressCacheMpoaRequestId
wfmpsIngressCacheMpoaRequestId.description: The request ID contained in the MPOA resolution request from the local Ingress MPC.

wfmpsIngressCacheNhrpRequestId.name: wfmpsIngressCacheNhrpRequestId
wfmpsIngressCacheNhrpRequestId.description: The request ID which this MPS generates to identify the NHRP resolution request.

wfmpsIngressCacheServiceCategory.name: wfmpsIngressCacheServiceCategory
wfmpsIngressCacheServiceCategory.description: The request ID which this MPS generates to identify the NHRP resolution request.

wfmpsIngressSlot.name: wfmpsIngressSlot
wfmpsIngressSlot.description: The Slot number of the slot on which this MPS is instantiated.

wfmpsEgressCacheTable.name: wfmpsEgressCacheTable
wfmpsEgressCacheTable.description: This table contains information regarding the Egress MPOA Server Cache Table.

wfmpsEgressCacheEntry.name: wfmpsEgressCacheEntry
